    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150213>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Distributional map of five species of Enneapterygius examined in this study." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150213/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150222>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Illustrations of mandibular pore system of Enneapterygius gracilis and Enneapterygius minutus. A double symphyseal mandibular-pores (3 + 2 + 3) (Enneapterygius gracilis, AMS I. 25500-005, male, 19.5 mm SL), B single symphyseal mandibular-pore (mandibular pore formula: 3 + 1 + 3) (Enneapterygius minutus, BMNH 1961.10.20.1, female, 20.4 mm SL) Bars represent 1 mm" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150222/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150224>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Photographs of fresh (A, B, D, E) and preserved (C, F) specimens of Enneapterygius minutus. A–C KAUM–I. 62853, male, 19.5 mm SL, Ishigaki-jima Island, Yaeyama Islands, Japan; D–F KAUM–I. 62851, female, 21.4 mm SL, same locality as KAUM–I. 62853" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150224/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150226>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Photographs of preserved specimens of Enneapterygius minutus. A BMNH 1961.10.20.1, lectotype of E. minutus, female, 20.4 mm SL, Apia, Western Samoa; B USNM 51800, holotype of Enneapterygius tusitalae, male, 18.5 mm SL, Apia, Upolo Island, Samoa; C USNM 51799, holotype of Enneapterygius pardochir, male, 21.2 mm SL same data as USNM 51800; D FMNH 17388, holotype of Enneapterygius punctulatus, male, 20.8 mm SL, Wala Island, Vanuatu" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150226/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10150228>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Photographs of type specimens of species currently synonymized with E. philippinus. a ZMA 112.506, lectotype of Tripterygium callionymi, 20.9 mm SL, Sulawesi Island, Indonesia; b FMNH 17494, holotype of Enneapterygius waigiensis, male, 17.2 mm SL, Waigeo Island, Indonesia; c ANSP 72062, holotype of Enneapterygius fuligicauda, male, 18.2 mm SL, Aguni-jima Island, Japan; d USNM 51802, holotype of Enneapterygius cerasinus, female, 19.6 mm SL, Upolu Island, Samoa" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10150228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

